id: pm-kf5q
title: Harden history replay and compact diff against malformed patch entries
description: "Sentry PM-CLI-1G and PM-CLI-1H show TypeError crashes when history replay/compact diff receives an entry whose patch is missing or not iterable. Duplicate check: searched for Sentry history diff replay patch undefined map buildDiffEntries; only closed history/replay items matched, so this is a new post-merge hotfix under storage/history."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:history","area:observability",hotfix,sentry
created_at: "2026-06-09T19:56:03.514Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-09T20:01:20.943Z"
author: codex-implementation-agent
parent: pm-o2kc
resolution: Hardened history replay and compact history diff against missing or malformed patch arrays that caused Sentry PM-CLI-1G and PM-CLI-1H.
expected_result: Malformed legacy history patch fields no longer crash history replay or compact history output.
actual_result: normalizeReplayPatchOps now returns a safe filtered array for unknown patch payloads; compact history uses it and tests cover missing patch arrays.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-09T20:01:20.059Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Evidence: fixed Sentry PM-CLI-1G/PM-CLI-1H by normalizing non-array/malformed history patch payloads to a safe filtered patch op list and using the same normalizer for compact history diff entries. Verification passed: focused history tests (2 files, 45 tests), pnpm typecheck, pnpm security:scan, pnpm audit --audit-level low, and full coverage (149 files, 2623 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
